Transform response variable

anlz_trans.Rd

Transform response variable prior to fitting GAM

anlz_trans(moddat, trans = c("boxcox", "log10", "ident"))

Arguments

moddat

input raw data, one station and paramater
trans

chr string indicating desired type of transformation, one of boxcox, log10, or ident (no transformation)

Value

moddat with the value column transformed as indicated

See also

Other analyze: anlz_avgseason(), anlz_backtrans(), anlz_fit(), anlz_gam(), anlz_perchg(), anlz_prdday(), anlz_prd(), anlz_smooth(), anlz_trndseason()

Examples

library(dplyr)
tomod <- rawdat %>% 
  filter(station %in% 32) %>% 
  filter(param %in% 'chl')
anlz_trans(tomod, trans = 'boxcox')
